sdp/verification/t-001@20260427t001208zb-verify.md:11:Implementation is correct against spec. `_poll_prediction` loops via `while True`, checking `status` each iteration: returns on `"succeeded"`, raises `GenerationError` on `"failed"` or `"canceled"` (with error detail), and raises `GenerationError` on timeout. The deadline is computed as `self._clock() + self._timeout_sec` at entry, honoring `self._timeout_sec` exactly. Sleep clamping via `min(POLL_INTERVAL_SEC, deadline - now)` prevents sleeping past the deadline. The clock is checked **after** the status check and **before** the sleep, so a non-terminal prediction already past deadline raises immediately without an extra sleep.
sdp/verification/t-001@20260427t001208zb-verify.md:22:- **`generate()` does not yet call `_poll_prediction`** (line 147–153). The method only submits; polling integration is deferred to a follow-up task. This is consistent with the prior state of the docstring ("polling... lands with T-001"), which itself notes the work as deferred. The task spec asked only for the private method, not the full wiring.
sdp/verification/t-001@20260427t001208zb-verify.md:35:No issues. No secrets or tokens used in the polling path. `getattr` with defaults prevents attribute injection from malformed prediction objects. `str(...)` coercion on `status` prevents non-string comparisons from breaking the loop.
sdp/verification/t-001@20260427t001208zb-verify.md:39:36/36 tests pass (`pytest tests/test_generation_replicate_retry.py -x`). All three new poll tests pass. No regressions in the prior 32 tests. The implementation is minimal — 25 lines for the method plus a 4-line helper — with no unnecessary abstraction.
sdp/verification/t-001@20260427t001208zb-verify.md:43:The auto-generated hardening items (`bootstrap_identity`, `FirstBootAnnouncer`, identity persistence) relate to a different subsystem (agent startup / identity minting) and do not apply to `_poll_prediction`. No action required for this task.
sdp/verification/t-001@20260427t001208zb-verify.md:49:- [ ] `generate()` does not call `_poll_prediction` yet — severity: **minor** (intentional deferral, but Lead should confirm a follow-up task exists to wire the full flow)
sdp/verification/t-001@20260427t001208zb-verify.md:57:3. Confirm that `generate()` wiring to `_poll_prediction` is tracked in a follow-up task — the current docstring still describes polling as deferred, which may confuse future readers once this branch merges.
