sdp/verification/t-003@20260515t214233z-verify.md:33:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-05-15T22:09:40.021Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1778882980021_1","parameters":{"file_path":"sdp/verification/t-003 @20260515t214233z-verify.md","content":"# Verification Report — T-003 @sdp/logs/Verify_T-003_20260515T214233Z_1778882941.log\n\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\n**Date:** 2026-05-15\n**Artifacts Reviewed:** tests/test_pal_agent.py, sdp/notifications.log, sdp/run-log.md\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation matches the requirements. `FakeSSHRunner` provides a reliable way to mock SSH command execution in `tests/test_pal_agent.py`, allowing the test suite to exercise remote-action logic (like router restarts and log inspection) without needing a live SSH environment. Assertions on `last_command` and status/summary outputs confirm the actions are triggering the expected commands.\n\n## Completeness\nThe solution covers the major remote-action paths used by the PAL agent:\n- `_restart_router_action`\n- `_inspect_logs_deep_action`\n- `_pause_shutdown_once_action`\n- `_resume_shutdown_action`\n- `_ssh_process_check_tool`\nEdge cases like missing credentials (resulting in \"skipped\" status) are also covered.\n\n## Consistency\nThe code follows established project patterns for testing and mocking. The use of `monkeypatch` to swap out the SSH runner is standard for this codebase.\n\n## Security\nNo security vulnerabilities were introduced. The fake runner avoids actual network connections, improving the security of the test environment by removing the need for real SSH keys or open ports during testing.\n\n## Quality\nThe code is clean, well-commented, and includes appropriate assertions. The transition to a fake runner significantly improves test reliability and speed for these components.\n\n## Issues Found\n- None.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe `FakeSSHRunner` is a great addition and could potentially be moved to a shared test utility if other modules need similar SSH mocking in the future.\n"}}
