sdp/verification/t-004@20260530t002730z-verify.md:28:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-05-30T00:58:39.888Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1780102719887_0","parameters":{"file_path":"sdp/verification/t-004@20260530t002730z-verify.md","content":"# Verification Report — T-004 @sdp/logs/Verify_T-004_20260530T002730Z_1780102642.log\n\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\n**Date:** Friday, May 29, 2026\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `promptclaw/asset_bus/store.py`\n- `tests/test_asset_bus_store.py`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation of `store.py` correctly resolves the asset bus root from the `DENIABLE_ASSET_BUS` environment variable, falling back to `~/deniable-asset-bus` as specified. It correctly handles tilde expansion. The `list_pending_requests` function correctly identifies request IDs that exist in the `requests/` directory but lack a corresponding `.result.json` in the `deliverables/` directory.\n\n## Completeness\nThe implementation covers all edge cases requested, including:\n- Missing `requests/` or `deliverables/` directories.\n- Non-conforming filenames or subdirectories in the `requests/` folder.\n- Sanitization of request IDs to prevent directory traversal or unsafe path access.\n- Sorting of pending request IDs.\n\n## Consistency\nThe code follows the established patterns in the `promptclaw/asset_bus` module. It uses standard library `pathlib` for path manipulations and `os` for environment variable access, consistent with the rest of the project.\n\n## Security\nRequest ID sanitization is implemented using `sanitize_request_id` (imported from `promptclaw.asset_bus.paths`), which ensures that only safe, alphanumeric-ish IDs are processed, mitigating potential path injection risks during pending request enumeration.\n\n## Quality\nThe code is well-structured, readable, and accompanied by a comprehensive test suite in `tests/test_asset_bus_store.py` (13 tests total) covering all functional requirements and edge cases.\n\n## Issues Found\n- None.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe implementation is clean and the test coverage is excellent. No further changes are required for this task.\n"}}
