sdp/verification/t-006@20260502t001347za-verify.md:11:{"type":"message","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:58:22.117Z","role":"user","content":"# Verification: Task T-006@20260502T001347Za\n\n**Task:** Add 'Lingering' section to ESCALATIONS.md documenting `loginctl enable-linger <user>` requirement so the systemd user service survives SSH logout; include verification command (`loginctl show-user <user> -p Linger`).\n**Tier:** T1\n\nYou are the VERIFY agent for this task. The LEAD agent has completed their work.\n\n\n## Review Checklist\n\n1. **Review recent commits:**\n   ```bash\n   git log --oneline -5\n   git diff HEAD~3 --stat\n   ```\n\n2. **Review code changes:**\n   ```bash\n   git diff HEAD~3\n   ```\n\n4. **Check ESCALATIONS.md** for any flagged issues.\n\n5. **Run the test suite:**\n   ```bash\n   pip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x\n   ```\n\n## Evaluation Criteria\n\nEvaluate the work against these five dimensions:\n\n1. **Correctness**: Does the output match the requirements/spec?\n2. **Completeness**: Are there gaps, missing edge cases, or unhandled scenarios?\n3. **Consistency**: Does the output follow established patterns and conventions?\n4. **Security**: Are there vulnerabilities, leaked secrets, or unsafe practices?\n5. **Quality**: Does the output meet the quality gates for this phase?\n\n## Output\n\nWrite your verification report and all findings to this exact path:\n`sdp/verification/t-006@20260502t001347za-verify.md`\nDo not use a different filename or directory.\n\nUse this format:\n\n```markdown\n# Verification Report — T-006@20260502T001347Za\n\n**Verify Agent:** [your agent name]\n**Date:** [today]\n**Artifacts Reviewed:** [list files reviewed]\n\n## Correctness\n[assessment]\n\n## Completeness\n[assessment]\n\n## Consistency\n[assessment]\n\n## Security\n[assessment]\n\n## Quality\n[assessment]\n\n## Issues Found\n- [ ] [Issue — severity: blocking/minor]\n\n## Verdict: [PASS | PASS WITH NOTES | FAIL]\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\n[specific items to address]\n```\n\nCommit the verification report.\n\n## Candidate Hardening (Auto-Generated)\n\nUse the recurring failure patterns below as mandatory hardening checks:\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Runtime does not invoke bootstrap_identity on startup, so the identity file is never guaranteed to be created automatically at first run. Severity: blocking.\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Add bootstrap_identity() invocation in startup flow (before FirstBootAnnouncer) so first boots mint and persist identity automatically..\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Ensure this path is used on both standalone and federated modes..\n- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: Add an integration test that exercises startup and verifies identity persistence between boots..\n- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: Re-run pip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x after wiring the startup path..\n"}
sdp/verification/t-006@20260502t001347za-verify.md:15:{"type":"tool_result","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:58:24.946Z","tool_id":"run_shell_command_1777687104801_0","status":"success","output":"13e87ec (HEAD -> feat/graceful-degradation) docs(escalations): add Lingering section for systemd user units [T-006@20260502T001347Za]\n5744343 verify(T-011@20260502T001347Z): PASS — beats/next endpoint verified\na63b8a2 docs(narrative-api): record beats verification [T-011@20260502T001347Z]\ncb0a4d8 feat(narrative-api): add beats next endpoint [T-011@20260502T001347Z]\n57ad898 test(narrative-api): cover beats endpoint [T-011@20260502T001347Z]\ndiff --git a/ESCALATIONS.md b/ESCALATIONS.md\nindex 172dd1b..c1c7754 100644\n--- a/ESCALATIONS.md\n+++ b/ESCALATIONS.md\n@@ -2,6 +2,32 @@\n \n Items requiring human review. Append-only per task.\n \n+## Lingering\n+\n+Systemd `--user` units (e.g. `cypherclaw-narrative-api.service`) only survive\n+after the operator's interactive session ends if **linger** is enabled for that\n+account. Without linger, the user systemd manager is torn down on SSH logout\n+and the service stops with it, defeating CN-013 / CN-015 (service must restart\n+automatically across reboot and remain active without an attached session).\n+\n+Enable linger once per host, as root:\n+\n+```bash\n+sudo loginctl enable-linger <user>\n+```\n+\n+Verify:\n+\n+```bash\n+loginctl show-user <user> -p Linger\n+# expected: Linger=yes\n+```\n+\n+If the output is `Linger=no`, the unit will not auto-start on boot and will\n+not survive logout — re-run the `enable-linger` command above. This is the\n+same gap captured in `sdp/verification/evidence/t-004@20260502t001347zc-narrative-api-status.md`\n+under \"Loginctl linger state for current user\".\n+\n ## T-003@20260502T001347Z (2026-05-02T00:13:47Z)\n \n - **Reason:** Deploy-side narrative event store is not checked into this workspace"}
