sdp/verification/t-001@20260530t002730z-verify.md:30:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-05-30T00:37:58.081Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1780101478080_0","parameters":{"content":"from pathlib import Path\nimport os\nimport pytest\nfrom promptclaw.asset_bus.paths import safe_deliverable_path, UnsafePathError\n\ndef test_symlink_escape():\n    # Setup a fake bus root\n    bus_root = Path(\"test_bus_root\").absolute()\n    bus_root.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    \n    request_id = \"req123\"\n    deliverables_dir = bus_root / \"deliverables\" / request_id\n    deliverables_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    \n    # Create a file outside the bus root\n    secret_file = Path(\"secret.txt\").absolute()\n    secret_file.write_text(\"sensitive data\")\n    \n    # Create a symlink inside the deliverables dir pointing outside\n    link_path = deliverables_dir / \"bad_link\"\n    if link_path.exists():\n        link_path.unlink()\n    os.symlink(secret_file, link_path)\n    \n    print(f\"Bus root: {bus_root}\")\n    print(f\"Deliverables dir: {deliverables_dir}\")\n    print(f\"Link path: {link_path} -> {link_path.resolve()}\")\n    \n    # Now try to access it via safe_deliverable_path\n    # Note: safe_deliverable_path calls sanitize_target_path which rejects \"bad_link/..\" or similar\n    # But what if we just ask for \"bad_link\"?\n    \n    try:\n        resolved = safe_deliverable_path(bus_root, request_id, \"bad_link\")\n        print(f\"Resolved (unexpectedly): {resolved}\")\n    except UnsafePathError as e:\n        print(f\"Caught expected error for direct symlink: {e}\")\n\n    # cleanup\n    link_path.unlink()\n    secret_file.unlink()\n    import shutil\n    shutil.rmtree(bus_root)\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    test_symlink_escape()\n","file_path":"verify_symlink.py"}}
sdp/verification/t-001@20260530t002730z-verify.md:32:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-05-30T00:37:59.401Z","tool_name":"run_shell_command","tool_id":"run_shell_command_1780101479401_0","parameters":{"description":"Run the symlink escape verification script.","command":"python verify_symlink.py"}}
sdp/verification/t-001@20260530t002730z-verify.md:43:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-05-30T00:38:15.758Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1780101495758_1","parameters":{"content":"# Verification Report — T-001 @sdp/logs/Verify_T-001_20260530T002730Z_1780101441.log\n\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\n**Date:** Friday, May 29, 2026\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `promptclaw/asset_bus/paths.py`\n- `promptclaw/asset_bus/__init__.py`\n- `tests/test_asset_bus_paths.py`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation correctly sanitizes request IDs and target paths.\n- `sanitize_request_id` enforces a strict regex `^[A-Za-z0-9][A-Za-z0-9._-]{0,127}$` and rejects `.` and `..`.\n- `sanitize_target_path` rejects absolute paths (POSIX and Windows), path traversal (`..`), NUL bytes, and empty paths. It normalizes backslashes to forward slashes.\n- `safe_deliverable_path` ensures that the resolved path stays within the `deliverables/<request_id>` directory using `Path.relative_to`, which correctly handles symlink-based escape attempts.\n\n## Completeness\nThe implementation covers all edge cases specified in the task:\n- Path-bearing request fields are sanitized.\n- Produced files land under `deliverables/<request_id>/` (via `deliverable_dir`).\n- Path traversal and absolute paths are rejected.\n- Comprehensive test coverage for these cases is provided in `tests/test_asset_bus_paths.py`.\n\n## Consistency\nThe code follows existing patterns:\n- Uses `pathlib.Path` and `PurePosixPath`.\n- Adheres to standard Python type hinting.\n- Exported via `promptclaw/asset_bus/__init__.py`.\n- Tests are consistent with the project's testing style.\n\n## Security\nSecurity is the primary focus of this task. The implementation is robust against:\n- Path traversal (`../`).\n- Absolute path coercion (`/etc/passwd`, `C:\\Windows`).\n- UNC path attacks (`\\\\server\\share`).\n- Symlink-based sandbox escapes (verified via `Path.resolve()` + `relative_to()` check).\n\n## Quality\nThe code is clean, well-documented, and passes all quality gates:\n- `pytest tests/test_asset_bus_paths.py` -> 14 passed.\n- `ruff check` -> clean.\n- `mypy` -> clean.\n\n## Issues Found\n- None.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe sanitization layer is robust and ready for integration into `store.py` and the producer runtime.\nCandidate hardening from the log was reviewed; while it mentions SuperCollider synthdefs (not directly related to path sanitization), the general principle of explicit parameter validation was observed in the `sanitize_*` functions.\n","file_path":"sdp/verification/t-001 @20260530t002730z-verify.md"}}
