ad Agent\n[specific items to address]\n```\n\nCommit the verification report.\n\n## Candidate Hardening (Auto-Generated)\n\nUse the recurring failure patterns below as mandatory hardening checks:\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Runtime does not invoke bootstrap_identity on startup, so the identity file is never guaranteed to be created automatically at first run. Severity: blocking.\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Add bootstrap_identity() invocation in startup flow (before FirstBootAnnouncer) so first boots mint and persist identity automatically..\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Ensure this path is used on both standalone and federated modes..\n- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: Add an integration test that exercises startup and verifies identity persistence between boots..\n- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: Re-run pip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x after wiring the startup path..\n"}
sdp/verification/t-006@20260530t002730z-verify.md:37:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-05-30T01:10:09.175Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1780103409174_1","parameters":{"file_path":"sdp/verification/t-006 @20260530t002730z-verify.md","content":"# Verification Report — T-006 @sdp/logs/Verify_T-006_20260530T002730Z_1780103315.log\n\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\n**Date:** Friday, May 29, 2026\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `promptclaw/asset_bus/store.py`\n- `tests/test_asset_bus_manifest_entry.py`\n- `promptclaw/asset_bus/__init__.py`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation of `asset_manifest_entry` in `promptclaw/asset_bus/store.py` matches the requirements:\n- Hashing: Uses `hashlib.sha256()` with 1MB chunked reading for memory efficiency.\n- Size: Uses `asset.stat().st_size` to record byte count.\n- Relative Paths: Uses `asset.relative_to(root).as_posix()` to ensure portable, relative paths.\n- Error Handling: Correctly raises `UnsafePathError` if an asset is outside the `bus_root`.\n- Interface: Returns a dictionary with `path`, `type`, `bytes`, `sha256`, and `meta`.\n\n## Completeness\nThe task is complete:\n- Edge cases like empty files, large files (multiple chunks), and nested directories are handled and tested.\n- `meta` pass-through (with defensive copy) is implemented.\n- Path sanitization via `resolve()` ensures `~` and symlinks are handled before relative path calculation.\n\n## Consistency\nThe code follows established patterns:\n- Uses `pathlib.Path` for all path manipulations.\n- Consistent with other `asset_bus` modules (e.g., `paths.py`).\n- Exported correctly in `asset_bus/__init__.py`.\n\n## Security\n- Enforces bus-root relative paths to prevent absolute path leakage in manifests.\n- Prevents access to files outside the bus root via `UnsafePathError`.\n- Uses SHA-256 for integrity verification.\n\n## Quality\n- Code is well-documented with docstrings.\n- Test suite is comprehensive, covering all functional aspects and error conditions.\n- Ruff and Mypy checks pass with no issues.\n\n## Issues Found\n- None.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nImplementation is solid. The use of `.as_posix()` ensures manifest portability across different OS environments.\nRegarding the Candidate Hardening for `bootstrap_identity`: This library-level task does not touch the runtime startup flow, so `bootstrap_identity` was not added to these files. However, `asset_bus` remains compatible with the identity system.\n"}}
